    {
      "id": "mrcgicsfzhuwfi89fy9",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1595,
      "y": 830,
      "strokeColor": "#40c057",
      "text": "2. Ler logs — \"O que está acontecendo?\"",
      "fontSize": 15,
      "angle": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": null,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "locked": false,
      "seed": 1,
      "versionNonce": 1,
      "updated": 1,
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "fontFamily": 2,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "width": 339,
      "height": 20
    },
    {
      "id": "mrcgict4fqrd3du73uf",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1595,
      "y": 858,
      "text": "\"Mostre os últimos 50 logs do pod\n<nome-do-pod> e me diga se há algo anormal.\"\n\n🔧 Tool: MCP Kubernetes -> kubectl logs\n🧠 Modelo: Identifica stack traces, erros\nde conexão, timeouts e pattern matching\n\n💡 MCP retorna os logs. Modelo encontra o\npadrão que você precisaria grep + grep",
      "fontSize": 12,
      "angle": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": null,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "locked": false,
      "seed": 1,
      "versionNonce": 1,
      "updated": 1,
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
