    {
      "id": "mrcgicvhy39c9j8boh9",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1135,
      "y": 1085,
      "strokeColor": "#fd7e14",
      "text": "3. Eventos — \"Qual a história do cluster?\"",
      "fontSize": 15,
      "angle": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": null,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "locked": false,
      "seed": 1,
      "versionNonce": 1,
      "updated": 1,
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "fontFamily": 2,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "width": 365,
      "height": 20
    },
    {
      "id": "mrcgicw4pvvifnqcf2d",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1135,
      "y": 1113,
      "text": "\"Quais eventos recentes aconteceram no\ncluster? Agrupe por tipo e destaque warnings.\"\n\n🔧 Tool: MCP Kubernetes -> kubectl get events\n🧠 Modelo: Agrupa por tipo, filtra warnings,\ndá contexto temporal e correlaciona eventos\n\n💡 kubectl get events é uma parede de texto.\nO modelo transforma em linha do tempo legível.",
      "fontSize": 12,
      "angle": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": null,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "locked": false,
      "seed": 1,
      "versionNonce": 1,
      "updated": 1,
